<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4533&amp;p=39662#p39662"><![CDATA[
If you want to turn the SEROM board to SBROM (aka allowing 64kb PRG and 64kb CHR, the maximum available if you only want to deal with 28-pins chips only) you'll only have to disconnect pin 1 to VCC and tie it to PRG A15 on the MMC1, which should be extremely simple to do.<br /><br />Why Nintendo did different boards for SEROM and SBROM to me is a complete mystery. I see no reason why a 32kb chip shouldn't work on SBROM (without rewiring). The same question remains for SCROM and SHROM, which seems also identical exept for pin 1 of the PRG.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Thu Nov 06, 2008 10:36 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
